/*
 * ============================================================================
 * Sprite dispatch tables — the heart of the per-frame sprite system
 * ============================================================================
 * kSpriteActiveRoutines : per-tick handler keyed on sprite_type[k] (0..242).
 *   Called every frame for every live sprite slot. The handler reads/writes
 *   the slot's sprite_* fields and emits OAM. NULL entries (only at index 3
 *   here) are illegal types — the framework treats them as bugs.
 *
 * Many adjacent entries point to the same function because related sprite
 * types (e.g. 0x04..0x07 pull-switch variants, 0x44 / 0x66..0x69 wall
 * cannons, the absorbable pickup family 0xD9..0xE2) share one handler that
 * disambiguates internally on sprite_type[k].
 *
 * The "Trampoline N entries" markers preserve a peculiarity of the original
 * ROM: the source assembly used long-call trampolines every ~48..68 entries
 * because the dispatch JSL ran into bank-boundary limits. We keep the
 * comments to make cross-referencing with the disassembly easier.
 */
